│ ## Initial Observations ##                                                                                                                                        │
│                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ The reproducer is already minimized. Based on my experience in debugging these bugs, the issue is likely introduced by the *first transformation*, or due to      │
│ incorrect analysis information feeding into it.                                                                                                                   │
│ Here, the *first transformation* means the *first transformation point* that modifies the IR in the pass regardless of whether it's in the                        │
│ `autofix/build/llvm-build/106780/bin/opt -p loop-vectorize -mtriple riscv64-linux-gnu -mattr=+v,+f -S /tmp/reprod_vueg54sm.l` module or other modules.            │
│ #### Opt Information ####                                                                                                                                         │
│                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ To gather more insight, I ran `opt` to inspect both the transformations and the analysis results. Below are the command and the resulting log:                    │
│                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                           │
│ $ bin/opt -p loop-vectorize -mtriple riscv64-linux-gnu -mattr=+v,+f -S --debug-only= /tmp/reprod_vueg54sm.ll                                                      │
│ opt: llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorize.cpp:7366: llvm::VectorizationFactor llvm::LoopVectorizationPlanner::computeBestVF(): Assertion                   │
│ `(BestFactor.Width == LegacyVF.Width || planContainsAdditionalSimplifications(getPlanFor(BestFactor.Width), CostCtx, OrigLoop)) && " VPlan cost model and legacy  │
│ cost model disagreed"' failed.                                                                                                                                    │
│                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                               │
│                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ From this log, I identified the first transformation point as:                                                                                                    │
